# Lipids

> [!Ontology]
> up:: [[Cards/Biomolecules\|Biomolecules]]
> jump:: [[Cards/Golgi Apparatus\|Golgi Apparatus]]
> down:: 

> [!Definition] Definition
> Lipids are a class of organic molecules that are insoluble in water but are soluble in nonpolar solvents such as chloroform or ether.

- The [[Cards/Golgi Apparatus\|Golgi Apparatus]] is the organelle that synthesises lipids.
## Lipid Structure

<svg version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 617 438" width="617" height="438" filter="invert(93%) hue-rotate(180deg)" class="excalidraw-svg"><symbol id="image-adb7a6d2b7e4928b60a7fa3591f7d007771fbbce"><image width="100%" height="100%" href="data:image/png;base64,"/></symbol>  <!-- svg-source:excalidraw -->    <defs>    <style class="style-fonts">      @font-face {        font-family: "Virgil";        src: url("https://excalidraw.com/Virgil.woff2");      }      @font-face {        font-family: "Cascadia";        src: url("https://excalidraw.com/Cascadia.woff2");      }      @font-face {        font-family: "Assistant";        src: url("https://excalidraw.com/Assistant-Regular.woff2");      }    </style>      </defs>  <g transform="translate(10 10) rotate(0 298.5 209)"><use href="#image-adb7a6d2b7e4928b60a7fa3591f7d007771fbbce" filter="invert(100%) hue-rotate(180deg) saturate(1.25)" width="597" height="418" opacity="1"/></g></svg>

The structure of a lipid consists of three parts: a glycerol backbone, two fatty acid chains attached to the carboxyl end of the glycerol, and a phosphate group attached to the other end of the glycerol in some lipids, such as phospholipids. The fatty acids can vary in length and saturation, which affects the fluidity and flexibility of the lipid molecule.
